BIB                 13         42
TITLE      Measurement of thermal neutron capture cross section
            of 71Ga with dual monitor foils and covariance
            analysis
AUTHOR     (P.Panikkath, N.Otuka, Y.Iwamoto, P.Mohanakrishnan)
INSTITUTE  (3INDMNP,3ZZZIAE,2JPNJAE)
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,55,91,2019)
INC-SOURCE (AM-BE) Am-Be source in concrete bunker
            (4E+7 neutrons/sec/4pi)
SAMPLE     (31-GA-71,NAT=0.3989) Ga2O3
            Bare:       101+/-0.5 mg, 0.012 cm thick
            Cd-covered: 108+/-0.5 mg, 0.013 cm thick
           (79-AU-197,NAT=1.) Elemental
            Bare:       124.3+/-0.6 mg, 0.005 cm thick
            Cd-covered: 125.7+/-0.6 mg, 0.005 cm thick
           (25-MN-55,NAT=1.) Mn(83wt%)-Cu
            Bare:       49.7+/-0.2 mg, 0.005 cm thick
            Cd-covered: 49.4+/-0.2 mg, 0.005 cm thick
METHOD     (ACTIV) Iradiated for 5 days (Ga+Mn) or 32 days (Au),
            and counted for 2500 to 60000 sec.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Relative efficiency of 30% calibrated by a
            152Eu source
CORRECTION Corrected for
            - Coincidence summing effect,
            - Neutron self-shielding,
            - Gamma attenuation.
           Capture of scattered neutrons is considered as
            negligible.
ADD-RES    The off-diagonal mean of the thermal cross sections
            determined with Au and Mn monitor foils: 4.04+/-0.27 b
COMMENT    By P.Panikkath and N.Otuka (2019-08-14):
            Three typos found in the manuscript after publication:
            1. 0.73 instead of 0.71 for the correlation
               coefficient between two thermal cross sections
               (Table 6).
            2. 7.89% instead of 8.09% for the total uncertainty
               in the thermal cross section determined with the
               Mn monitor foil (Table 6).
            3. 4.04+/-0.27 b instead of 4.05+/-0.27 b for the
               off-diagonal weighted mean of the thermal cross
               section (Table 7).
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by Priyada Panikkath (2019-06-14)
HISTORY    (20190613C) On
